How to Use the Custom ACF Font Awesome Icon Dynamic Tag in Elementor
Save the files
Place both files (plugin.php and class-acf-fontawesome-icon-tag.php) in a folder inside your /wp-content/plugins/ directory.
For example, create a folder named:
elementor-acf-fontawesome-icon

Activate the plugin
Go to your WordPress admin panel → Plugins, find the plugin named:
“Elementor Dynamic Tag – ACF Font Awesome Icon”, and click Activate.

Add the ACF field
Make sure you have an ACF field of type “Font Awesome Icon Picker” created in your Field Group.
Set the Return Format to “Icon Class”.
Use a field name like: custom_icon

Use in Elementor
Open the Elementor editor, add a Text or Icon widget.

Click the dynamic tags icon (⚙️) next to the field.

Choose “ACF Font Awesome Icon” from the dynamic tag list.

Enter the ACF field name you used (e.g., custom_icon) in the settings.
